索尼宣布它已在Housemarque＆＃39; S往返于年轻PlayStation 5控制台上的最高型材专用之一后获得了芬兰独立开发人员房马马马塔克。 Housemarque历史悠久地与索尼控制台，追溯到2007年和＃39; Super Stardust HD上的Super Stardust HD，并通过PS4推出突出突发resogun运行。 Housemarque也是2017 PS4双棒射击射线Nex Machina的工作室，ars＆＃39; Sam Machovech当时在他的年度比赛中致敬。在一个非索尼控制台上的最后一个高等优惠的游戏是2008年＆＃39; s的小记忆高尔夫：它在Xbox 360上发了推送。＆＃34;它很难想象一个没有来自拥有优惠品的游戏机平台，＆＃34; PlayStation Studios负责人Hermen Hulst在与华盛顿邮报采访中说。 ＆＃34;他们创造的游戏与我们所拥有的一切都如此不同，所以我喜欢我们能提供的经验的多样性。＆＃34;
 还与华盛顿邮报，Housemarque联合创始人和董事总经理Ilari Kuittinen表示，索尼在谈判之前也在谈判时收购工作室。 Kuittinen还表示，索尼向小团队提供了援助，该团队开发了代理人，这为以前为更简单的街机射击者闻名的工作室的工作室代表了3D勘探和高端生产价值。
    赫斯特说，鉴于收购，符合收购，但＆＃34显然，他们将希望扩展其大约80人的工作室;显然他们不会成为一个巨大的500人团队 - 这不是目标。＆＃34;索尼没有披露在购买时购买的金额。
 索尼＆＃39;最后一个主要的博彩收购是2019年购买蜘蛛侠开发商失眠症2.29亿美元。同时，微软，最近在贝塞斯达软工上花了数十亿岁才能在Scooping Speconauts 2 Studio Double Fine和其他几个独立工作室，包括亡灵实验室（腐烂状态），游乐场（Forza Horizo​​ n），忍者理论（Hellblade），和强制游戏（我们很高兴）。
 霍尔特说，他对英国GQ说道，他并没有看到索尼参与An＆＃34;军备赛＆＃34;两个控制台制造商尽可能多地保护多个独家工作室。 ＆＃34;我们＆＃39;对我们带来的开发人员来说，＆＃39非常有选择。他说。 ＆＃34;我总是在寻找具有类似一套价值观，类似的创造性野心的人，与我们的团队一起工作，我们可以进一步投资并帮助成为创造者的团队。它＆＃39;不喜欢我们＆＃39;重新解决，只是做随机收购。他们非常非常有针对性的团队获得我们所知的团队。＆＃34;
 ＆＃34;随着[索尼]的支持及其支持我们的工作室系列，我们可以真正成长到业内人士中，并展示了软房，没有限制，＆＃34; Kuittinen在宣布收购的博客文章中写道。 ＆＃34;我们迫不及待地想向大家展示即将到来的几年将在商店中，我们希望迎来更持久的回忆和下一个四分之一世纪和超越的令人振奋的标题。＆＃34;

note_en:
Sony has  announced that it has acquired Finnish indie developer Housemarque just two months after  the launch of Housemarque&#39;s  Returnal as one of the highest-profile exclusives on the young PlayStation 5 console.  Housemarque has a long history with Sony consoles, dating back to 2007&#39;s   Super Stardust HD on the then-new PlayStation 3 and running through  PS4 launch standout  Resogun. Housemarque is also the studio behind the 2017 PS4 twin-stick shooter  Nex Machina, which Ars&#39; Sam Machkovech  gave an honorable mention in his Games of the Year list at the time. The last Housemarque game on a non-Sony console was 2008&#39;s little-remembered  Golf: Tee it Up on the Xbox 360. &#34;It’s pretty hard to imagine a launch of a PlayStation platform without there being something from Housemarque,&#34; Hermen Hulst, the head of PlayStation Studios, said in  an interview with The Washington Post. &#34;The games they create are just so different from everything else we’ve got, so I love the diversity of the experiences that we’re able to offer.&#34;
 Also speaking to The Washington Post, Housemarque co-founder and Managing Director Ilari Kuittinen said Sony was in talks to acquire the studio even before  Returnal was released. Kuittinen also said that Sony offered assistance to the small team developing  Returnal, which represented a turn toward 3D exploration and high-end production values for a studio previously known for simpler arcade shooters.
    Hulst said Housemarque will be looking to expand its approximately 80-person studio in light of the acquisition but that &#34;obviously they’re not going to be a giant 500-man team—that’s not the goal.&#34; Sony is not disclosing the amount spent on the Housemarque purchase.
 Sony&#39;s last major gaming acquisition was the  2019 $229 million purchase of  Spider-Man developer Insomniac. Microsoft, meanwhile, recently  spent billions on Bethesda Softworks a few years after  scooping up  Psychonauts 2 studio Double Fine and  several other indie studios, including Undead Labs ( State of Decay), Playground Games ( Forza Horizon), Ninja Theory ( Hellblade), and Compulsion Games ( We Happy Few).
 Speaking to British GQ, Hulst said he doesn&#39;t see Sony engaging in an &#34;arms race&#34; where both console-makers try to secure as many exclusive studios as possible. &#34;We&#39;re very selective about the developers that we bring in,&#34; he said. &#34;I&#39;m always looking for people that have a similar set of values, similar creative ambitions, and work very well with our team that we can further invest in and help grow as creators. It&#39;s not like we&#39;re going around and just making random acquisitions. They’re very, very targeted acquisitions of teams that we know well.&#34;
 &#34;With the backing of [Sony] and its family of studios supporting us, we can truly grow into our place in the industry and show what Housemarque can create with no limitations,&#34; Kuittinen  wrote in a blog post announcing the acquisition. &#34;We can’t wait to show everyone what will be in store in the upcoming years, and we hope to usher in more lasting memories and exhilarating titles for the next quarter century and beyond.&#34;
